<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-262-005 </DOCNO><DOCID>09 471 225</DOCID><JOURNAL>The Seybold Report on Publishing Systems  Sept 24 1990 v20 n2p24(2)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Seybold Publications Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>CCI Europe, based in Denmark, faring well. (only the US firm CCIis defunct)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   CCI Europe (foreign operations)CCI Corp. (management).andO;Topic:     ComparisonDivestmentFailureGrowthCompaniesEuropeUnited States.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>CCI Europe, based in Denmark, faring well In our recent review of Penta'snew-generation system, we commented on the fact that &quot;CCI disappeared fromthe market after the founders left to form Magna.&quot;andP;  As our American readersknew well, we were referring to the U.S.andP;  company by the name of CCI.andM;In fact, as we should have mentioned, there is also a European company,formally called CCI Europe, that had been split from the U.S.andP;  firm a coupleof year earlier.andP;  We have been asked to reassure our European readers thatCCI Europe currently is faring very well, having just won some big newspaperorders and recording four straight impressive years.andM;We apologize for any confusion we may have caused.andO;</TEXT></DOC>